⚡ Nazarine DCSmart Energy Management SystemNazarine DC is a high-performance, full-stack IoT platform designed for real-time telemetry, historical data aggregation, and predictive insights. Engineered to bridge the gap between physical hardware (ESP32) and high-level data visualization, it provides a robust pipeline for smart home and industrial energy grids.🚀 Key AdvantagesHigh-Fidelity Telemetry: Achieves sub-second latency via WebSockets for instantaneous power, voltage, and current feedback.Hardware-in-the-Loop: Seamlessly interfaces with ESP32 microcontrollers using standardized JSON telemetry schemas.Deep-Time Aggregation & Global Finance: Backend integration converts raw power (kW) into accumulated energy (kWh) and carbon metrics (kg CO2), while supporting dynamic global currency mapping (₦, $, €, £) and processing up to 2 years of macro-aggregated monthly and yearly billing cycles.NLP Expert System: Features an embedded AI Support assistant capable of scanning live database telemetry to detect load spikes, warn of under-usage, and calculate real-time operating costs.Machine Learning Forecasting: Infrastructure is optimized for Pandas-ready data structures, and now features a fully deployed Scikit-Learn predictive engine. It utilizes a Random Forest Regressor to map out decision trees and accurately forecast the next 24 hours of grid load.Off-Peak Optimization: The system mathematically scans historical patterns to suggest the most cost-effective 3-hour window for running high-load appliances.🛠️ Tech StackLayerTechnologyFrontendHTML5, Tailwind CSS, JavaScript (ES6+), Chart.js BackendPython 3.x, FastAPI, Uvicorn (ASGI), WebSockets Machine LearningPandas, NumPy, Scikit-LearnDatabaseSQLite3 (Persistent Time-Series Storage) 💻 Local Setup & Execution1. PrerequisitesEnsure you have Python 3.7+ installed.2. Install DependenciesRun the following command to install the core backend and Machine Learning requirements:Bashpip install fastapi uvicorn pydantic pandas scikit-learn numpy requests
3. Initialize the DatabaseSeed your database with 2 years of realistic historical telemetry to populate the deep-time macro charts:Bashpython seed_db.py
Note: This generates a nazarine_memory.db file in your directory.4. Launch the Backend ServerBashuvicorn main:app --reload
The server will be live at http://127.0.0.1:8000.5. Access the DashboardOpen energy_dashboard.html directly in your browser.💡 Pro-Tip: Avoid VS Code "Live Server" extensions to prevent infinite refresh loops caused by frequent database updates. Opening the file via file:/// is recommended.🔌 Simulated Hardware TestingIf no physical ESP32 is connected, you can use the built-in simulator to beam realistic residential telemetry directly to the API:Open a new terminal window.Run the simulator script:Bashpython mock_esp32.py
The dashboard will instantly snap to life with live electrical metrics.Developed as a professional mechatronics and aerospace-grade energy monitoring solution.